Reasoning: The paper discusses the functions of a leader node in Ad hoc networks, particularly in Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs) and Internet of Things (IoT). This topic falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the challenges and opportunities in leader election algorithms, which can be categorized under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the need for fault-tolerant and robust algorithms, which can be categorized under Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
